WEBVTT

00:02.436 --> 00:03.502
[ Remote clicks ]

00:03.504 --> 00:05.037
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:07.574 --> 00:10.442
♪ I don't care what you say! ♪

00:11.778 --> 00:13.779
♪ I'm gonna do what I want
all day! ♪

00:13.781 --> 00:16.415
♪ I'm the king of the world!
I'm the king of the world! ♪

00:16.417 --> 00:18.350
♪ I'm the king of the world!
I'm the king of the world! ♪

00:18.352 --> 00:22.755
♪ I'm the king of the world!
I'm the king of the world! ♪

00:29.029 --> 00:30.629
[ Bell rings ]

00:30.631 --> 00:31.964
Treehouse games!

00:31.966 --> 00:33.765
Super fun treehouse games!

00:33.767 --> 00:36.301
Crawdad races.
Kiddie pool. A ladder.

00:36.303 --> 00:38.970
Yep, we got it all!
-Hmm? What's this?

00:38.972 --> 00:40.105
Huh?

00:40.107 --> 00:41.906
A throwing rock?

00:41.908 --> 00:42.974
Sounds fun.

00:42.976 --> 00:45.243
Oh, it is.
It's very fun.

00:45.245 --> 00:46.778
Can I bring a friend?

00:46.780 --> 00:48.814
[ Giggling ]
- Huh?

00:48.816 --> 00:50.248
No grownups?

00:50.250 --> 00:52.250
[ Laughs ]
You can't even come!

00:52.252 --> 00:56.388
I got you!
-Aw, but...why?

00:56.390 --> 00:57.822
Why?

00:57.824 --> 00:59.758
♪♪

01:02.896 --> 01:05.930
Very nice.

01:05.932 --> 01:08.633
[ Giggling ]

01:08.635 --> 01:09.568
[ Thud! ]

01:09.570 --> 01:13.504
Hey, shark attack!
Ha-ha-ha-ha!

01:13.506 --> 01:14.773
Oh, no!

01:14.775 --> 01:16.741
Oh, no, it's scary!

01:16.743 --> 01:18.744
Oh, no!

01:18.746 --> 01:21.012
I'm dying!

01:21.014 --> 01:23.949
My guts are coming out!
Bleh!

01:23.951 --> 01:28.186
I'm becoming a shark, too!
[ Laughs evilly ]

01:28.188 --> 01:30.655
But we're vampire sharks!

01:30.657 --> 01:32.024
Watch out!

01:32.026 --> 01:33.658
We're gonna get you!

01:33.660 --> 01:35.360
[ Laughing ]

01:35.362 --> 01:38.597
Aw, guys, let's try to be aware
of the reading nook.

01:38.599 --> 01:41.132
-It's Old Man Belson!
-Hey!

01:41.134 --> 01:43.468
Knock it off!
Dumb babies.

01:43.470 --> 01:45.437
Clarence: We got Dilben!

01:45.439 --> 01:48.339
-Chomp, chomp, chomp!
-What...

01:48.341 --> 01:50.375
...is that?

01:53.046 --> 01:55.714
That's a mustache.

01:55.716 --> 01:58.049
The undeniable sign
of puberty.

01:58.051 --> 02:00.885
-Gilben's got a mustache?
-Mm-hmm.

02:00.887 --> 02:04.223
Man, that thing's
lookin' good, Gilben.

02:04.225 --> 02:06.658
[ Crow caws ]

02:06.660 --> 02:07.892
I want one.

02:07.894 --> 02:10.896
-Whatever. I've seen better.
-Oh, no! No, no!

02:10.898 --> 02:12.964
Clarence: Heh.
How's this even possible?

02:12.966 --> 02:15.400
I didn't know it was going
to happen so soon.

02:15.402 --> 02:18.136
We're halfway to being adults,
if you think about it.

02:18.138 --> 02:19.238
Oh, no.

02:19.240 --> 02:20.572
Walk with me.

02:20.574 --> 02:22.040
My taxes were very
tax-y this year.

02:22.042 --> 02:23.242
It's the grown-ups
department.

02:23.244 --> 02:24.976
I need 16 divorces
by last Tuesday!

02:24.978 --> 02:26.577
You!
Take off that tie!

02:26.579 --> 02:28.346
You!
Put on that tie! Okay!

02:28.348 --> 02:29.747
Sir, the investors are filing
a suit against --

02:29.749 --> 02:31.416
No, not now! Time is
money and money's walking,

02:31.418 --> 02:32.817
and I'm walking,
so I'm money!

02:32.819 --> 02:34.753
Did you locate the escrow?
-Yes, sir!

02:34.755 --> 02:35.753
[ Crow cawing ]

02:35.755 --> 02:36.821
Get off me!

02:36.823 --> 02:38.923
Oh, Clarence,
don't forget tutor time!

02:38.925 --> 02:40.158
[ Humming ]

02:40.160 --> 02:42.060
Oops, you almost
got this one right.

02:42.062 --> 02:43.394
I gotta hand it to you,
Clarence.

02:43.396 --> 02:44.763
You've been treating
your homework

02:44.765 --> 02:46.231
with a lot
of responsibility.

02:46.233 --> 02:47.765
Oh!
Your shoe's untied.

02:47.767 --> 02:50.168
I shouldn't got no
responsibilities.

02:50.170 --> 02:52.670
Babies got no
responsibilities.

02:52.672 --> 02:55.907
[ Gasps ] Babies got
no responsibilities!

02:55.909 --> 02:57.409
[ Laughs ]

02:59.613 --> 03:01.947
Huh? What?
Clarence, no!

03:01.949 --> 03:04.349
What are you doing?!
You've undone all your progress!

03:04.351 --> 03:05.784
Where are you going?

03:05.786 --> 03:08.787
Now, now, Clarence.
Let's not do anything rash.

03:08.789 --> 03:11.356
Just take the trash back
to the can, close the lid,

03:11.358 --> 03:13.558
and forget all of this
ever happened.

03:13.560 --> 03:15.293
I don't understand
what has gotten into you,

03:15.295 --> 03:18.296
but -- don't you dare unzip
that bag!

03:18.298 --> 03:19.797
Clarence.

03:19.799 --> 03:21.065
[ Chortles ]

03:21.067 --> 03:22.200
[ Doorbell rings ]

03:22.202 --> 03:23.435
Now your pants are off!

03:23.437 --> 03:24.803
That's it, I'm out!

03:24.805 --> 03:27.272
Talk to me when you're ready
to grow up!

03:27.274 --> 03:29.140
[ Laughs ]

03:29.142 --> 03:31.076
Hey, man.

03:31.078 --> 03:32.810
Hello, Sumo.

03:32.812 --> 03:35.079
You want
some appie sauce?

03:35.081 --> 03:37.215
No, I got something
even better.

03:37.217 --> 03:39.484
-Yeah?
-Jesse Hacksaw III.

03:39.486 --> 03:40.986
Found it in my brother's
backpack.

03:40.988 --> 03:42.554
You wanna watch it?

03:42.556 --> 03:44.656
Uhhh, um.
No way.

03:44.658 --> 03:47.659
That stuff's for grown-ups.
I'd rather watch this.

03:47.661 --> 03:50.328
Woman:<i> Do you know</i>
<i>where the Frisbee is?</i>

03:50.330 --> 03:51.929
Oh, behind the couch,
Goolia!

03:51.931 --> 03:55.099
<i>Where could it be?</i>
<i>I can't find it.</i>

03:55.101 --> 03:56.835
You sure you don't
want to come?

03:56.837 --> 03:59.671
[ Singsong voice ] She'll make
you scream for days.

03:59.673 --> 04:03.508
No, this wholesome kid fun
is all I need.

04:03.510 --> 04:05.109
<i>I don't see it.</i>

04:05.111 --> 04:06.611
-Come on, Goolia!
<i>-Do you?</i>

04:06.613 --> 04:09.180
It's right there. Just look.
It's behind the couch.

04:09.182 --> 04:12.150
Just look behind the couch!
[ Sobs ]

04:12.152 --> 04:13.518
<i>Is it behind the couch?</i>

04:13.520 --> 04:17.188
[ Crying ] Just look
at your surroundings.

04:17.190 --> 04:18.756
[ Humming ]

04:18.758 --> 04:19.824
What?

04:19.826 --> 04:22.494
[ Sighs ]
Okay, very cute, Clarence.

04:22.496 --> 04:24.262
What's with the trash
and everything?

04:24.264 --> 04:25.864
The coop is a train wreck.

04:25.866 --> 04:27.466
[ Chickens squawking ]

04:27.468 --> 04:30.502
Maybe the chickens did it.
[ Chuckles ]

04:30.504 --> 04:33.705
Clarence, what's going on?
You always do your chores.

04:33.707 --> 04:34.873
I don't know.

04:34.875 --> 04:37.042
I'm just a kid
- and I'm never gonna grow up.

04:37.044 --> 04:38.443
Ever.

04:38.445 --> 04:41.212
What? [ Chuckles ]
- Being a grown-up ain't so bad.

04:41.214 --> 04:42.514
Come on.

04:42.516 --> 04:44.616
You ain't got anyone
tellin' you what to do.

04:44.618 --> 04:46.818
You know, you get to stay up
as late as you want.

04:46.820 --> 04:48.886
Being an adult is actually
pretty cool.

04:48.888 --> 04:51.623
[ Snoring ]

04:51.625 --> 04:53.057
Hmm.

04:53.059 --> 04:54.892
[ Grunting ]

04:54.894 --> 04:57.128
Stupid.

04:57.130 --> 04:59.397
Ooh.

04:59.399 --> 05:01.466
♪ Yeah, that's right ♪

05:01.468 --> 05:03.334
♪ I'm a grown-up ♪

05:03.336 --> 05:05.904
Feels good to be
a grown-up.

05:05.906 --> 05:07.071
[ Slurps ]

05:07.073 --> 05:08.473
Mwah!

05:08.475 --> 05:10.908
♪ It feels good
to be a grown-up ♪

05:10.910 --> 05:13.912
♪ I can finally do ironing ♪

05:13.914 --> 05:16.081
♪ It's time I can tell
I'm grown-up ♪

05:16.083 --> 05:20.751
♪ Grown-up, grown-up,
grown-up ♪

05:20.753 --> 05:22.420
<i>Money's so tight these days.</i>

05:22.422 --> 05:25.923
<i>I actually caught my kids</i>
<i>playing hide-and-go-broke.</i>

05:25.925 --> 05:27.258
[ Chuckles ]

05:27.260 --> 05:29.026
Money.

05:29.028 --> 05:32.196
Allowance cuts
for kids -- approved.

05:32.198 --> 05:34.499
Gross income?
That's disgusting!

05:34.501 --> 05:35.866
[ Laughs ]

05:35.868 --> 05:38.403
Wait, Clarence,
- are those my actual taxes?

05:38.405 --> 05:39.704
You can't play with that!

05:39.706 --> 05:41.539
And you can't talk
to a grown-up like that!

05:41.541 --> 05:43.108
That's a time-out for you!

05:43.110 --> 05:44.276
Oh, it is, huh?

05:44.278 --> 05:46.111
That's what you think, huh?
No.

05:46.113 --> 05:48.946
Beep-beep, beep-beep.
Hey, look at that.

05:48.948 --> 05:50.581
I'm late for work.

05:50.583 --> 05:53.518
What the?
[ Sighs ]

05:53.520 --> 05:55.053
Yeah, well,
those mortgages

05:55.055 --> 05:57.522
aren't gonna shmortgage
themselves, Debra.

05:57.524 --> 05:59.257
Oh, Jeff, come in.

05:59.259 --> 06:00.458
Great, great, great.

06:00.460 --> 06:02.460
Yeah, just pay me up
in the "manana."

06:02.462 --> 06:03.961
Is that my reading nook?

06:03.963 --> 06:05.863
Please, sit down.

06:05.865 --> 06:07.932
O-kay.

06:07.934 --> 06:10.135
Jeff --
May I call you Jeff?

06:10.137 --> 06:12.804
I called you in today
to let you know personally

06:12.806 --> 06:14.639
that I'm a real
grown-up now.

06:14.641 --> 06:16.974
Made a deposit
and everything.

06:16.976 --> 06:19.144
[ Squeak! ]

06:19.146 --> 06:22.079
Any Joe Schmoe from Idaho
can make a deposit.

06:22.081 --> 06:23.548
The real sign of an adult

06:23.550 --> 06:25.983
is being responsible
for somebody else.

06:25.985 --> 06:29.754
Jeff, I'm ready for
- the ultimate responsibility.

06:29.756 --> 06:31.990
I wanna have a kid.

06:31.992 --> 06:33.291
Uh...

06:33.293 --> 06:35.159
Will you help me?

06:35.161 --> 06:37.562
H-How do you mean?

06:37.564 --> 06:39.330
Is a bonnet
really necessary?

06:39.332 --> 06:41.332
Hush now.
Papa's gotta learn.

06:41.334 --> 06:42.733
[ Pop! ]
- Blah!

06:42.735 --> 06:44.402
You're lucky
my mom's a doula

06:44.404 --> 06:46.271
so we can borrow
all this baby stuff.

06:46.273 --> 06:47.806
Are you ready?

06:47.808 --> 06:48.974
[ Grunting ]

06:51.010 --> 06:54.345
Time for your
first "chawenge."

06:54.347 --> 06:56.181
Man: Chawenge one.

06:56.183 --> 06:57.849
Wah! Wah, wah! Wah!

06:57.851 --> 07:00.452
Aw, what's wrong,
Baby Jeffy?

07:00.454 --> 07:01.953
Wah!!

07:01.955 --> 07:03.087
Wah, wah!

07:03.089 --> 07:05.990
I-I got a big meeting tomorrow,
Baby Jeffy.

07:05.992 --> 07:07.091
What is it?

07:07.093 --> 07:09.461
Babies can't talk.
You gotta figure it out.

07:09.463 --> 07:11.362
Wah-ah!
Wah, wah, wah, wah!

07:11.364 --> 07:13.531
♪ Go to sleep ♪

07:13.533 --> 07:15.032
♪ Go to sleep ♪

07:15.034 --> 07:16.134
Wah!

07:16.136 --> 07:18.135
♪ Go to sleep!
Go to sleep! ♪

07:18.137 --> 07:19.437
Go back to sleep!

07:19.439 --> 07:21.305
Clarence!
That is too rough!

07:21.307 --> 07:24.142
But --
- Agh, you have to feed me.

07:24.144 --> 07:25.477
Chawenge two.

07:25.479 --> 07:26.945
Clarence: Hmm.

07:26.947 --> 07:28.847
Where's the milk go
in this thing?

07:28.849 --> 07:32.050
-[ Coughs ]
-Maybe it goes...

07:32.052 --> 07:34.386
[ Air hissing ]

07:34.388 --> 07:36.621
Cough, cough!
Ahem!

07:36.623 --> 07:37.889
Cough, cough!

07:37.891 --> 07:39.057
Oh.

07:39.059 --> 07:41.225
Uh, here.
Swallow the pills!

07:41.227 --> 07:42.994
C'mon!
Get 'em down!

07:42.996 --> 07:44.829
Pwuh! Wrong!

07:44.831 --> 07:46.898
Always call
the pediatrician first!

07:46.900 --> 07:49.200
You failed to have a doctor
diagnose the cough.

07:49.202 --> 07:51.403
You gave your baby
the wrong medicine.

07:51.405 --> 07:53.671
And now I'm dead.
Bleh.

07:53.673 --> 07:56.574
How's my favorite grandson?

07:56.576 --> 07:58.142
Man: Chawenge three.

07:58.144 --> 07:59.477
You gotta clip my nails.

07:59.479 --> 08:00.645
I can't do it myself.

08:00.647 --> 08:01.879
Hold still now.

08:01.881 --> 08:04.248
Sheesh, who taught you
to decorate?

08:04.250 --> 08:06.017
I-I can't talk right now, Ma.

08:06.019 --> 08:07.485
Fine, ignore me.

08:07.487 --> 08:08.553
What's happenin'?

08:08.555 --> 08:10.554
Clarence is all grown up.

08:10.556 --> 08:13.224
Ohhh. [ Chuckles ]

08:13.226 --> 08:14.425
I'm over here now!

08:14.427 --> 08:16.560
Daddy, take me
to the park!

08:16.562 --> 08:17.695
Just a second, sweetie.

08:17.697 --> 08:19.764
But I wanna go now!!

08:19.766 --> 08:21.399
What's up, babies?

08:21.401 --> 08:22.867
Oh, um, hi, Belson.

08:22.869 --> 08:25.103
You wanna be my assistant?

08:25.105 --> 08:26.938
No way.
You're not the boss of me.

08:26.940 --> 08:28.740
If anything,
I'm the boss of you.

08:28.742 --> 08:30.675
And you're fired!

08:30.677 --> 08:33.110
[ Gasps ]
Clarence, is this true?

08:33.112 --> 08:35.346
Did mama's boy get fired?

08:35.348 --> 08:36.547
Your baby's getting away.

08:36.549 --> 08:39.050
Oh.
Jeffy, come back!

08:39.052 --> 08:40.451
I wanna play.

08:40.453 --> 08:41.752
[ Cries ]

08:41.754 --> 08:43.955
Hold on, Baby Percy.

08:43.957 --> 08:45.123
Baby?

08:45.125 --> 08:47.625
[ Whining ] What's that
supposed to mean?

08:47.627 --> 08:50.061
Oh, bein'
responsible's tough.

08:50.063 --> 08:52.730
Look who's maturing
into an angsty teen.

08:52.732 --> 08:54.365
You wanna steal
some cars?

08:54.367 --> 08:55.432
Yeah!

08:55.434 --> 08:56.968
[ Both imitate engines roaring ]

08:56.970 --> 08:59.303
Uh, uh, no driving
in the house, please!

08:59.305 --> 09:00.871
Chump!

09:00.873 --> 09:02.607
This place is a pigsty!

09:02.609 --> 09:03.875
-Uh, uh, okay.
-Ha!

09:03.877 --> 09:07.212
My car-insurance rates
are goin' way up!

09:07.214 --> 09:10.882
-Papa! Bath time!
-Vroom, vroom, vroom, vroom!

09:10.884 --> 09:12.717
Come on, Clarence,
clip my nails!

09:12.719 --> 09:14.652
Come on!
-Okay.

09:14.654 --> 09:16.153
Belson: Do it, Clarence!
Do it!

09:16.155 --> 09:18.222
[ Thudding ]

09:18.224 --> 09:19.991
[ All gasping ]

09:29.969 --> 09:30.768
[ Gasps ]

09:30.770 --> 09:33.304
My fingie! Waah!!

09:33.306 --> 09:35.306
Oh, no, no, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no, no!

09:35.308 --> 09:38.176
Clarence, you're a worse mother
than I was!

09:38.178 --> 09:39.244
I want nine fingers too!

09:39.246 --> 09:41.479
Yeah, I'm callin'
child services.

09:41.481 --> 09:43.847
Nooo!!

09:43.849 --> 09:46.518
Gah!
I can't do this, okay?

09:46.520 --> 09:48.752
I'm not all grown up
like Gilben!

09:48.754 --> 09:51.623
[ Mechanical screeching ]

09:53.192 --> 09:54.159
Gilben.

09:55.695 --> 09:59.164
Held back?
For two years?

10:00.200 --> 10:02.333
So, even though you're older
than us,

10:02.335 --> 10:04.669
you still like to hang out
with us kids?

10:04.671 --> 10:06.003
We heard Gilben
the first time.

10:06.005 --> 10:07.372
So what you're saying is,

10:07.374 --> 10:09.874
that no matter how long
my mustache gets

10:09.876 --> 10:11.509
or how much my bald spots grows

10:11.511 --> 10:14.512
or how pruny my face becomes,
I can just stay a kid?

10:14.514 --> 10:17.047
I don't ever have to be
a boring old grown-up?

10:17.049 --> 10:18.950
Is that what you're saying,
Gilben?

10:18.952 --> 10:20.818
That is exactly
what he just said.

10:20.820 --> 10:24.856
So, I could just be some sort
of adult baby?

10:24.858 --> 10:26.557
Does such a thing
even exist?

10:26.559 --> 10:29.326
Hmm. It's even bigger
than I thought.

10:29.328 --> 10:30.862
Hey!

10:30.864 --> 10:33.231
Hey, you kids!
I know you're up there!

10:33.233 --> 10:34.833
Mr. Reese?

10:34.835 --> 10:36.868
Okay, I know it said
No Adults Allowed,

10:36.870 --> 10:40.338
but I'm still a kid
at heart! You know?

10:40.340 --> 10:43.174
And I just wanna throw somethin'
at that rock!

10:43.176 --> 10:44.709
Uhh.

10:44.711 --> 10:46.577
Is that so wrong?

10:46.579 --> 10:48.546
[ Kids murmuring ]

10:48.548 --> 10:51.182
I...I guess not.

10:53.185 --> 10:54.185
Whoo-hoo!

10:54.187 --> 10:55.686
[ Panting ]

10:55.688 --> 10:57.155
[ Grunting ]

10:57.157 --> 10:58.255
Oh!

10:58.257 --> 11:00.225
[ Kids chuckling ]

11:04.663 --> 11:06.564
♪ Early to bed ♪

11:08.101 --> 11:10.402
♪ Early to rise ♪

11:11.571 --> 11:13.672
♪ Picking my nose ♪
